      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine with VarioCam Plus timing. This enthusiast-spec example is equipped with the G96 6-speed manual transaxle, ensuring direct mechanical connection and precise gear selection. The chassis maintains excellent kinematics thanks to refreshed suspension bushings and a well-sorted multi-link rear geometry. Crucial preventative maintenance is documented, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Air-Oil Separator (AOS). While the aesthetic shows honest patina consistent with its age, the powertrain remains tight with strong compression across all cylinders and a communicative hydraulic steering rack. This is a driver-focused machine optimized for lateral grip and linear power delivery.",
